          "translation": "The children are playing in the garden.",
          "hint": "child, plural",
          "display_order": 4
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Ich habe zwei {{answer}} zu Hause.",
          "answer": "Katzen",
          "translation": "I have two cats at home.",
          "hint": "cat, plural",
          "display_order": 5
        },
        {
          "sentence": "Die {{answer}} sind neu.",
          "answer": "Autos",
          "translation": "The cars are new.",
          "hint": "car, plural (-s)",
          "display_order": 6
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Definite articles (der / die / das)",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Point to a specific thing",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 3,
      "explanation": "Der for masculine (der Mann), die for feminine (die Frau), das for neuter (das Haus) — and die again for every plural (die Kinder). The article is the gender's uniform: memorize noun and article as one word.",
      "culture_note": "",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: German articles",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_articles"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: German grammar",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_grammar"
        }
      ],
