    {
      "title": "Indefinite articles (ein / eine)",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Mention something for the first time",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 4,
      "explanation": "Ein for masculine and neuter (ein Mann, ein Haus), eine for feminine (eine Frau). There is no plural indefinite article — plural just drops it: Das sind Bücher. The endings change with case; that story starts with the accusative later in this path.",
      "culture_note": "",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: German articles",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_articles"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wiktionary: ein (German)",
          "url": "https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/ein#German"
        }
      ],
